FlyXCDB - Drosophila melanogaster extracellular domain database

FlyXCDB is a database that contains extracellular (XC) domain information for protein-coding genes of Drosophila melanogaster (Dmel) from FlyBase (version FB2015_03).

For each Dmel gene, a cluster of proteins was constructed including orthologs and their nonidentical isoforms in 12 Drosophila genomes. A set of Drosophila XC domains were defined based on manual analysis of Pfam domains in Drosophila cell surface and secreted (CSS) proteins. The resources used in manual analysis include predictions of signal peptide, transmembrane segment, and GPI signal sequence, Pfam domains detected by HMMER3 and HHsearch, FlyBase (FB2015_03) Gene Ontology (GO) cellular component terms, and literature. Each Drosophila XC domain entry corresponds to a single Pfam domain or a group of evolutionarily related Pfam domains.

Below is the information table for Dmel genes with XC domains. The table for all Dmel protein-coding genes is here (slower to load).

This table is sorted by the occurrence frequencies of Drosophila XC domains in the following order.
     P (red)     - XC domains likely involved in protein-protein interactions
     S (darkred) - XC domains mainly found in signaling molecules such as growth factors, hormones, and neuropeptides
     B (cyan)    - XC domains likely involved in binding non-protein molecules or groups (e.g. carbohydrates and lipids)
     E (magenta) - XC domains of enzyme homologs
     R (orange)  - XC enzyme regulatory and inhibitory domains
     U (blue)    - putative XC domains with unknown molecular function
     N (black)   - other domains (mostly non-extracellular)

Column names are:
CMT - manually assigned cell membrane topology (CMT) category for protein isoform(s) of a Dmel gene
     E for secreted protein
     S for single-pass type I/III transmembrane protein with C-terminus in cytosol
     T for single-pass type II transmembrane protein with N-terminus in cytosol
     M for multi-pass transmembrane protein
     G for GPI-anchored protein

GeneID   -  FlyBase gene id, with link to FlyBase
Name     -  FlyBase gene name, with link to a page containing predictions for each protein
#SEQ     -  number of orthologs and non-identical protein isoforms, with link to multiple sequence alignment
SP       -  fraction of signal peptide predicted by SignalP4.0 (truncation site: 70, default) among orthologs and nonidentifical isoforms
SP200    -  fraction of signal peptide predicted by SignalP4.0 (truncation site: 200, allowing longer signal peptide prediction)
SP_PHO   -  fraction of signal peptide predicted by Phobius
ave_SP   -  average of SP, SP200 and SP_PHO (red: >=0.5)
TM_PHO   -  average number of transmembrane segments predicted by Phobius (blue: >=0.5)
ave_GPI  -  average of GPI-anchor prediction fractions by PredGPI and FragAnchor (orange: >=0.5)
XC       -  extracellular domains detected by HMMER3. Domains in brackets belong to a homologous domain group (treated as a single XC domain) with group name before their brackets.
Others   -  other domains detected by HMMER3
XC_HH    -  extracellular domains detected by HHsearch
Others_HH - other domains detected by HHsearch
GO_CC    -  FlyBase (FB2015_03) Gene Ontology (GO) Cellular Component terms
Click the column names will sort the table accordingly, which may take some time.
